{"questionId":"2681073","questionHtml":"<p>Determine if the events <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></math> are independent. Justify your answer.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1 (using <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>|</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>)</mo></math>)</strong></p>\n<p>recognition that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></math> are independent if <strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>|</mo><mi>M</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>)</mo></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em> (M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>≠</mo><mfrac><mn>100</mn><mn>160</mn></mfrac></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>so they are not independent&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2 (using <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>·</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>∩</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></math>)</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to find the product <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>×</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>M</mi><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>×</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>D</mi><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>100</mn><mn>160</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>72</mn><mn>160</mn></mfrac><mo>≠</mo><mfrac><mn>24</mn><mn>160</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>32</mn></mfrac><mo>≠</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>20</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>100</mn><mn>160</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>88</mn><mn>160</mn></mfrac><mo>≠</mo><mfrac><mn>76</mn><mn>160</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>11</mn><mn>32</mn></mfrac><mo>≠</mo><mfrac><mn>19</mn><mn>40</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>so they are not independent&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award <em><strong>R0A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2681073","referenceCode":"23M.2.SL.TZ1.8d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Determine if the events A and M are independent. Justify your answer.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}